title: 500mA, autofill to RUN mode
Shift summary: Monday swing
text: SUMMARY: Post-holiday restart as planned. There is currently 500mA stored in SPEAR with autofill on and beamlines closed. The SPEAR knob box doesn't work. There are a few crate alarms. Two CEBAF bulk supplies have zero readback on their EDM panel but the supplies are working. Beam was lost once due to a power dip. SAPEs 246 and 271 (part 1) were done. Fill rate is about 35mA/minute, and calculated efficiency is above 100%. INJECTOR: The injector was being brought up at the start of the shift. There was 200-250mV to full energy (beam on PR-2) by 4:30pm. BTS beam became intermittent at one point during SPEAR injection; tweaking the booster RF phase seems to have resolved the issue. Two of the four CEBAF bulks have zero readbacks on the injector power supply display, though the supplies are clearly working fine. SAPE 246 (ACM checks) was performed per BAS. SPEAR: The ring was filled in steps once the injector was ready, reaching 500mA by around 5:30pm. Autofill was turned on for 5-minutes top-ups. Beamlines remain closed for now. Stored beam was lost at 10:36pm when many SPEAR supplies and the RF station tripped off as a result of a power dip. Faults were cleared and the ring was refilled to 500mA without trouble. The B117 knob box does not work properly. Nothing can be assigned, and it displays "disabled" whether the disable button is engaged or not. The Hettel knob (SPEAR-booster RF phase) cannot be adjusted. There are crate alarms for 132-CCB4C1 (temp) and SPEARPROD2 (unclear why). Also, SPEAR-ACSW5 appears to have no connectivity (all white boxes with no values). SAPE 271 part 1 (SCI checks) was performed per BAS.
